author: Curtis Duffield
title: Sandy Valley closing in on historic season
text: Sandy Valley closing in on historic season The buzz in the community is grower stronger by the day as the Sandy Valley football team looks to make history. Comment CantonRep.com sports writer Posted Oct. 22, 2015 at 3:42 PM The buzz in the community is grower stronger by the day as the Sandy Valley football team looks to make history. The Cardinals, who have seven wins in a season for the first time since 1992 and just the fourth time ever, are moving closer to their first-ever appearance in the state playoffs. Individual season records are falling in their wake.
